\maketitle

\section*{Introduction}
This document outlines the prioritized features for the AI-Enhanced Sales Forecasting System development, along with high-level effort estimates. The features are categorized into high, medium, and low priorities to guide the development process effectively.

\section*{High Priority Features}
High priority features are crucial for the initial launch, providing the core functionalities necessary for basic operations.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{p{4.5cm}p{8cm}r}
\toprule
\textbf{Feature} & \textbf{Description} & \textbf{Effort Estimate} \\
\midrule
Data Import and Integration & Import historical sales, customer demographics, and market trends. & High (3 weeks) \\
Machine Learning Model & Integrate advanced AI models for accurate sales forecasting. & High (6 weeks) \\
Real-time Executive Dashboard & Implement a dashboard with KPIs for real-time performance monitoring. & High (5 weeks) \\
User Authentication System & Secure access with user authentication and authorization. & High (3 weeks) \\
Customizable Forecasting Parameters & Allow customization of forecast parameters via a user-friendly interface. & High (4 weeks) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\section*{Medium Priority Features}
Medium priority features enhance the system by adding significant value without being critical for the initial launch.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{p{4.5cm}p{8cm}r}
\toprule
\textbf{Feature} & \textbf{Description} & \textbf{Effort Estimate} \\
\midrule
User Customizable Dashboards & Enable personalized dashboard creation for users. & Medium (4 weeks) \\
Admin Configuration Interface & Admin interface for system settings and compliance. & Medium (3 weeks) \\
Customer Demographics & Enhance forecasts with customer demographic data. & Medium (5 weeks) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\section*{Low Priority Features}
Low priority features are considered nice-to-have and can be added post-launch to improve or extend the functionality.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{p{4.5cm}p{8cm}r}
\toprule
\textbf{Feature} & \textbf{Description} & \textbf{Effort Estimate} \\
\midrule
Feedback Loop for Model Improvement & Continuous improvement mechanism for forecasting accuracy. & Low (4 weeks) \\
Integration with External Business Systems & CRM, ERP, and inventory management integration for comprehensive insights. & Low (5 weeks) \\
Usability Testing and Interface Enhancements & Refine user interfaces based on feedback. & Low (2 weeks) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}


